if you are looking to make your own you will need the following parts, 10K potentiometer, an on off switch, 2 barrel jack connecters, a 5k ohm resistor, M2 3mm(length) by 3.2mm(outer diameter), shrink wrap is optional but id highly reccomend it, you also may want electrical tape to insulate everything to prevent a short
To make the pedal
Step 1 start by taking copper sheildeng tape and line the inside of the shell
Step 2 start by pressing the 4 heat inserts into the 4 corners 
Step 3 start placing the components into the shell to cut your wire to length
Step 4 start soldering according to the diagram(be sure to atatch your grounding wire to the tape)
Step 5 screw in the back and your done, you should now have a working battery sag pedal if you did everything correctly!
